
'''= Synergia is an network of activist-scholars that has organized two learning retreats in Tuscany and is working on a MOOC for social change.'''

URL = https://synergiainstitute.wordpress.com/

=Description=

"The Synergia Institute is an international network of individuals and organizations that unites academics, social activists, practitioners and policymakers in a common effort to articulate, advocate, and implement models of economic and social practice that transition societies to a new model of political economy that is sustainable, democratic, socially just, and based on the principles of co-operation and the common good.

Synergia unites education, training, and praxis in both online and face-to-face encounters that integrate peer-to-peer learning and knowledge sharing as a key feature of our social change work."
(https://synergiainstitute.wordpress.com/2018/01/27/about-synergia-institute/)

